Whether the results are great or not, they merely represent how far we have gone since we started our journey. However, as Nido Qubein once said, â€œYour present circumstances donâ€™t determine where you can go; they merely determine where you start.â€ Wherever youâ€™re going is simply where youâ€™re going to spend the next 4 years. But lifeâ€™s quite long. Itâ€™s where you want to go that really matters in the end.

Finally, we have spent tons of time preparing for the big exam. Our life should be different due to our efforts. Additionally, we canâ€™t know if the situation that seems lucky to us now remains the same in the future, neither does the one that seems to be unlucky now. And, hopefully, everything will be wonderful in the future.

Back home.

Getting used to everything about flying.

Still, I can remember the motto of LIFE magazine mentioned in The Secret Life of Walter Mitty.
"To see the world, things dangerous to come to, to see behind walls, to draw closer, to find each other and to feel. That is the purpose of life."

We are the change that we seek, so never be afraid to have a dream.
This big adventure is going to end but it create a dream for me, a big dream which point out the direction of my life.

I tend to overthink and care too much about trivial things.

Really frustrated about souvenirs.

Back to Sydney.

Finally here.

Lucky it's been sunny after midday.
Another thing beyond description.
Thank you Karen, Gary, David, Shannon and two little beautiful creatures.
It's my pleasure to meet all of you.

Finally escaped from the 7 hour train seat, people's snore and kids' noise.
And it's only me so far!
The adventure continues with a early morning train.

Night adventure ðŸŒ
Tired but fulfilled.
And tomorrow's another one.
Keep going.

Don't know why everything makes me feel so frustrated tonight.
Luggage unpacked / dilemma / leaving Sydney / nothing for present / unknown tiredness and so on.
Anyway, thank you Ed.

My secret business.
Love everything about it.
A walk with the silly little dog.
Never get sick of going to a beach but the more eager you are to jump into the sea.

Tuck myself in the bed at 00:00 and then wake up at 02:00 to watch the FIFA World Cup with my lovely cousin.
Unconsciously fell asleep in the 2nd half ðŸ˜´

After the whale watching was a small version of family gathering.
Really happy to see those people again!
Last but not least, finally found the suitable alcohol drink for me.
nice music / peaceful beach / lovely people.
Finally got the book I want and had the time to write down what I've done for the past few days.
Didn't think of anything but take off my socks and shoes when I saw the beach.

First taste of night life in Sydney.
Love everyone I met today.

Family Day.
A party for my aunt's birthday.
Going to the pub tonight, woohoo~

Countless seagulls peeping at your food.
Just saw two of them stealing others sashimi.

Feeling worth it for walking the whole day.
Start thinking about taking buses.

Good morning.
Btw, finally accessible for Facebook.

After a 2 hour sleep,
finally heading to the next stop in this adventure, Sydney.
The airport was so empty in the early morning.
Feeling happy with so many foreign people's company.

Today we come across an individual who behaves like an automaton, who does not know or understand himself, and the only person that he knows is the person that he is supposed to be, whose meaningless chatter has replaced communicative speech, whose synthetic smile has replaced genuine laughter, and whose sense of dull despair has taken the place of genuine pain. Two statements may be said concerning this individual. One is that he suffers from defects of spontaneity and individuality which may seem to be incurable. At the same time it may be said of him he does not differ essentially from the millions of the rest of us who walk opinion this earth. - The 7 Habits of Highly Effective People #katyreadinglog
